definitions.definition: A person or an animal that exhibits no symptoms of disease .
examples: After a 10-day observation period, group 1 was divided into subgroup 1A (symptomatics) and subgroup 1B ( asymptomatics ).

definitions.definition: Preceded by the : people or animals that exhibit no symptoms of disease regarded collectively .
examples: At the end of the observation period, those who are still symptomatic require second-line treatment, whereas the asymptomatic are discharged.
